# Tooltip

> Small and lightweight hints that do not interrupt the flow.  
> **Status**: Beta


## Demo

### Hover Hint

Short hints with low intrusion.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="TooltipHoverDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxTooltip content="Hint">
      <TxButton variant="ghost">Hover me</TxButton>
    </TxTooltip>
    <TxTooltip content="Info">
      <TxButton variant="ghost">Info</TxButton>
    </TxTooltip>
  </template>
---
::

## Basic Usage
::TuffCodeBlock{lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxTooltip content="Copied">
      <TxButton variant="ghost">Copy</TxButton>
    </TxTooltip>
  </template>
---
::

## API (Lite)
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: content
    type: 'string'
    default: '-'
    description: 'Tooltip text'
  - name: trigger
    type: "'hover' | 'click' | 'focus'"
    default: "'hover'"
    description: 'Trigger mode'
  - name: placement
    type: 'string'
    default: 'top'
    description: 'Placement'
  - name: indicator
    type: 'boolean'
    default: 'false'
    description: 'Enable indicator dot'
  - name: indicator-placement
    type: "'panel' | 'reference'"
    default: "'panel'"
    description: 'Render indicator on panel or trigger'
  - name: indicator-variant
    type: "'dot' | 'pulse'"
    default: "'dot'"
    description: 'Indicator visual style'
  - name: open-delay
    type: 'number'
    default: '120'
    description: 'Open delay (ms)'
  - name: close-delay
    type: 'number'
    default: '80'
    description: 'Close delay (ms)'
---
::

## Design Notes
- Keep text short, avoid multiline.  
- Maintain light spacing from the trigger element.
- Tooltip now defaults to a background-free lightweight wrapper.

## Composite Patterns

### Tooltip Button

Icon button with a hint.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="TooltipButtonDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxTooltip content="Share">
      <TxButton icon="i-ri-share-line" circle />
    </TxTooltip>
  </template>
---
::

### Indicator

Show a notification marker either on the tooltip panel or directly on the trigger.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="TooltipIndicatorDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxTooltip content="Panel indicator" indicator indicator-variant="pulse" indicator-placement="panel">
      <TxButton variant="ghost">View notice</TxButton>
    </TxTooltip>

    <TxTooltip content="Reference indicator" indicator indicator-placement="reference" indicator-color="#f56c6c">
      <TxButton variant="ghost">System status</TxButton>
    </TxTooltip>
  </template>
---
::
